# SKILL: HubSpot API Integration
*Portable skill for HubSpot v1/v3 email sync, contact classification, thread classification, and rep attribution.*
*Tested on: clearsky-api Worker (v79y), 1,128 threads, 1,668 contacts*

## HubSpot API — Email Engagements (v1)
```javascript
// Paginated fetch — v1 engagements/paged (deprecated but still works)
const url = `https://api.hubapi.com/engagements/v1/engagements/paged?hapikey=${env.HUBSPOT_API_KEY}&limit=250&offset=${offset}`;
// Returns: { results: [{ engagement: { id, type, timestamp, ownerId }, associations: { contactIds, dealIds }, metadata: { from, to, cc, subject, text, html } }], hasMore, offset }

// Thread grouping — group by threadId or normalized subject
function groupEmailThreads(engagements) {
  const threads = {};
  for (const e of engagements) {
    const meta = e.metadata || {};
    const threadId = meta.threadId || normalizeSubject(meta.subject || '');
    if (!threads[threadId]) threads[threadId] = { id: md5(threadId), subject: meta.subject, emails: [] };
    threads[threadId].emails.push({
      id: e.engagement.id,
      from: (meta.from?.email || '').toLowerCase(),
      fromName: meta.from?.firstName ? `${meta.from.firstName} ${meta.from.lastName || ''}`.trim() : meta.from?.email,
      to: (meta.to || []).map(t => (t.email || '').toLowerCase()),
      cc: (meta.cc || []).map(c => (c.email || '').toLowerCase()),
      subject: meta.subject,
      body: meta.text || stripHtml(meta.html || ''),
      bodyHtml: meta.html,
      timestamp: new Date(e.engagement.timestamp).toISOString(),
      direction: e.metadata?.from?.email?.endsWith('@clearskyltd.com') ? 'outbound' : 'inbound',
      ownerId: e.engagement.ownerId
    });
  }
  return Object.values(threads);
}
```

## R2 Thread Storage
```
Bucket: clearsky-files
Path: hubspot/threads/{md5_thread_id}.json
Shape: { id, subject, contact_name, contact_email, company, pablo_project_id, last_activity, emails[] }
```
- D1 hubspot_threads stores lean metadata index (no thread_json for new syncs)
- Full email bodies stored in R2 only
- Thread detail: read from R2, fallback to D1 thread_json (legacy)

## Contact Classification — 5-tier Priority Engine
```javascript
function classifyContact(email, jobTitle, industry, lifecyclestage, leadStatus) {
  // Priority order:
  // 1. Domain match → internal (clearskyltd.com, leadingcarbon.com, maboroshi.com)
  // 2. Lifecycle stage → commercial_buyer (customer, opportunity, SQL, MQL)
  // 3. Lead status → commercial_buyer (open_deal, in_progress, connected)
  // 4. Domain match → operational (verra.org, dnv.com, bureauveritas.com, ey.com, etc.)
  // 5. Title keywords → operational/commercial_buyer/commercial_seller
  // 6. Industry match → commercial_buyer (oil/airlines/automotive) or seller (environmental/forestry)
  // 7. Fallback → unknown
  return { contact_type, method };
}
```

**Contact types:** `internal`, `commercial_buyer`, `commercial_seller`, `operational`, `unknown`

**Keyword lists:**
- OPERATIONAL_DOMAINS: verra.org, puro.earth, goldstandard.org, dnv.com, bureauveritas.com, sgs.com, deloitte.com, pwc.com, kpmg.com, ey.com, garrigues.com, cuatrecasas.com
- BUYER_TITLE_KW: sustainability, esg, carbon, climate, environment, procurement, offset, net zero, csr, responsibility
- SELLER_TITLE_KW: developer, origination, forest, reforestation, project manager, land use, conservation
- OPERATIONAL_TITLE_KW: lawyer, attorney, legal, notary, auditor, accountant, tax, counsel, solicitor, registrar, verifier, validator

## Thread Classification — 9-category Rules Engine
```javascript
function classifyThreadBySubject(subject, senderEmail, senderName, recipientsJson) {
  // Rule 1: noise — newsletters, automated, OOO (regex on subject)
  // Rule 2: internal — all participants from internal domains
  // Rule 3: commercial_active — pricing, offtake, LOI, contract, deal terms
  // Rule 4: commercial_prospecting — intro, meeting, follow-up, partnership
  // Rule 5: legal_ops — NDA, contract, agreement, clause, amendment
  // Rule 6: financial_ops — invoice, payment, wire, billing
  // Rule 7: project_ops — verra, puro, verification, methodology, PDD
  // Rule 8: market_intel — forwarded research, reports, analysis
  // Rule 9: admin — schedule, logistics, travel, expense
  // Fallback: unknown (needs Claude Haiku for ambiguous threads)
  return { thread_type, confidence: 'high'|'medium'|'low', method: 'subject_pattern'|'participant_check'|'no_pattern_match' };
}
```

**Thread types:** `commercial_active`, `commercial_prospecting`, `legal_ops`, `financial_ops`, `project_ops`, `market_intel`, `admin`, `internal`, `noise`, `unknown`

