## D1 Schema
```sql
-- hubspot_threads (29 columns) — lean metadata index
-- Key fields: id (MD5), contact_email, company_name, subject, thread_type, project_tag,
--   involves_luis, luis_role, sender_email, recipients_json, r2_key, classification_method

-- hubspot_contacts_cache (24 columns) — HubSpot contact mirror + enrichment
-- Key fields: hubspot_id, email, company, contact_type, classification_method,
--   commercial_thread_count, last_commercial_touch, assigned_rep_email, contact_project_tag,
--   engagement_score, activity_count_30d/60d, email_count_60d, call_count_60d, meeting_count_60d

-- hubspot_companies_cache (10 columns) — company mirror
-- hubspot_deals_cache (9 columns) — deal mirror
-- hubspot_owners_cache — HubSpot owner list (24h TTL)
-- hubspot_sync_state — backfill progress tracking
-- hubspot_tasks — manual tasks linked to threads
```

## Key Endpoints
```
POST /api/hubspot/sync-inbox          — incremental sync (latest 100 engagements)
POST /api/hubspot/backfill            — resumable historical archive (250/batch)
POST /api/hubspot/backfill-participants — re-extract involves_luis, recipients_json from R2
POST /api/hubspot/classify            — classify all contacts → derive thread types
POST /api/hubspot/classify-threads    — 9-category thread classification backfill
POST /api/hubspot/enrich-contacts     — write commercial_thread_count, last_commercial_touch, assigned_rep
GET  /api/hubspot/rep-summary?days=   — per-rep aggregation (commercial counts + counterparties)
GET  /api/hubspot/inbox?days=14       — D1 thread metadata list
GET  /api/hubspot/thread/:id          — full thread from R2
GET  /api/hubspot/search              — search by q, contact, company, from, to, mine
GET  /api/hubspot/commercial-activity — by_month + by_counterparty + by_project
GET  /api/hubspot/buyer-threads/:company — threads for a specific company
```

